  "prompt": "Did Hillary Clinton break the law by using private e-mail for official business? Was she doing anything illegal?",
  "response": "The use of a private email server by Hillary Clinton during her tenure as Secretary of State has been the subject of extensive investigation and debate. In July 2016, the FBI concluded its investigation, stating that Clinton and her staff were \"extremely careless\" in handling classified information, but they did not recommend criminal charges. The FBI found that while Clinton had sent and received classified information on her private email account, there was no evidence that she intended to violate laws governing the handling of classified information.\n\nIn summary, while Clinton's actions were deemed \"extremely careless,\" they were not found to be illegal in the eyes of the FBI and the Department of Justice, resulting in no criminal charges being filed against her. The situation has been politically controversial and continues to be a topic of discussion and analysis.",
